
1987-06-04

# Chief Complaint
- Tingling in Hands and Feet
- Thirst
- urinary frequency
- Cough
- Frequent Urination


# History of Present Illness
Stanley
 is a 74 year-old non-hispanic black male. Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), limited social contact (finding), not in labor force (finding), unhealthy alcohol drinking behavior (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), acute viral pharyngitis (disorder), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), viral sinusitis (disorder), social isolation (finding), stress (finding), severe anxiety (panic) (finding.

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a high socioeconomic background.
 Patient is a college graduate.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; paclitaxel 100 mg injection; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler; nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray; amoxicillin 250 mg / clavulanate 125 mg oral tablet; cisplatin 50 mg injection

# Assessment and Plan


## Plan




1987-05-26

# Chief Complaint
- Tingling in Hands and Feet
- Thirst
- urinary frequency
- Cough
- Frequent Urination


# History of Present Illness
Stanley
 is a 74 year-old non-hispanic black male. Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), limited social contact (finding), not in labor force (finding), unhealthy alcohol drinking behavior (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), acute viral pharyngitis (disorder), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), viral sinusitis (disorder), social isolation (finding), stress (finding), severe anxiety (panic) (finding.

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a high socioeconomic background.
 Patient is a college graduate.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; paclitaxel 100 mg injection; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler; nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray; amoxicillin 250 mg / clavulanate 125 mg oral tablet; cisplatin 50 mg injection

# Assessment and Plan


## Plan

The following procedures were conducted:
- renal dialysis (procedure)
- spirometry (procedure)
- pulmonary rehabilitation (regime/therapy)
The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]
- nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray
- 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet
- 120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler
- nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler
- 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler

The following procedures were conducted:
- renal dialysis (procedure)
The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]



1986-04-09

# Chief Complaint
- Tingling in Hands and Feet
- Thirst
- urinary frequency
- Cough
- Frequent Urination


# History of Present Illness
Stanley
 is a 73 year-old non-hispanic black male. Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), limited social contact (finding), not in labor force (finding), unhealthy alcohol drinking behavior (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), acute viral pharyngitis (disorder), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), viral sinusitis (disorder), social isolation (finding), stress (finding), severe anxiety (panic) (finding.

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a high socioeconomic background.
 Patient is a college graduate.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; paclitaxel 100 mg injection; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler; nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray; amoxicillin 250 mg / clavulanate 125 mg oral tablet; cisplatin 50 mg injection

# Assessment and Plan


## Plan

The following procedures were conducted:
- renal dialysis (procedure)
- spirometry (procedure)
- pulmonary rehabilitation (regime/therapy)
- assessment of health and social care needs (procedure)
The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]
- nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray
- 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet
- 120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler
- nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler
- 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler

The following procedures were conducted:
- renal dialysis (procedure)
- spirometry (procedure)
- pulmonary rehabilitation (regime/therapy)
- assessment of health and social care needs (procedure)
The patient was prescribed the following medications:
- 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]
- nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray
- 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet
- 120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler
- nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler
- 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler



1985-12-01

# Chief Complaint
- Tingling in Hands and Feet
- Thirst
- urinary frequency
- Cough
- Frequent Urination


# History of Present Illness
Stanley
 is a 73 year-old non-hispanic black male. Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), limited social contact (finding), not in labor force (finding), unhealthy alcohol drinking behavior (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), acute viral pharyngitis (disorder), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), viral sinusitis (disorder), social isolation (finding), stress (finding), severe anxiety (panic) (finding.

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a high socioeconomic background.
 Patient is a college graduate.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; paclitaxel 100 mg injection; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler; nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray; amoxicillin 250 mg / clavulanate 125 mg oral tablet; cisplatin 50 mg injection

Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), limited social contact (finding), not in labor force (finding), unhealthy alcohol drinking behavior (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), viral sinusitis (disorder), social isolation (finding), stress (finding), severe anxiety (panic) (finding.

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a high socioeconomic background.
 Patient is a college graduate.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; paclitaxel 100 mg injection; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler; nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray; amoxicillin 250 mg / clavulanate 125 mg oral tablet; cisplatin 50 mg injection

# Assessment and Plan

The patient was prescribed the following medications:

Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), limited social contact (finding), not in labor force (finding), unhealthy alcohol drinking behavior (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), viral sinusitis (disorder), social isolation (finding), stress (finding), severe anxiety (panic) (finding.

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a high socioeconomic background.
 Patient is a college graduate.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
120 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.044 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; nda020503 200 actuat albuterol 0.09 mg/actuat metered dose inhaler; 1 ml epoetin alfa 4000 unt/ml injection [epogen]; simvastatin 10 mg oral tablet; paclitaxel 100 mg injection; 24 hr metformin hydrochloride 500 mg extended release oral tablet; 60 actuat fluticasone propionate 0.25 mg/actuat / salmeterol 0.05 mg/actuat dry powder inhaler; nitroglycerin 0.4 mg/actuat mucosal spray; amoxicillin 250 mg / clavulanate 125 mg oral tablet; cisplatin 50 mg injection

# Assessment and Plan

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a high socioeconomic background.
 Patient is a college graduate.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications

Patient has a history of part-time employment (finding), limited social contact (finding), not in labor force (finding), reports of violence in the environment (finding), full-time employment (finding), victim of intimate partner abuse (finding), viral sinusitis (disorder), social isolation (finding), stress (finding), severe anxiety (panic) (finding.

# Social History
Patient is married. Patient is an active smoker and is an alcoholic.
 Patient identifies as heterosexual.

Patient comes from a high socioeconomic background.
 Patient is a college graduate.
Patient currently has Medicare.

# Allergies
No Known Allergies.

# Medications
